CLOCK_MODE().details: Machine-readable description of the clock as specified in ERC-6372.

castVoteWithOption(uint256,uint8).details: Cast a vote for a specific option in a multiple choice proposal. Encodes optionIndex into params for the internal cast vote function.

params.optionIndex: The index of the option to vote for

returns.balance: The weight of the cast vote

clock().details: Clock (as specified in ERC-6372) is set to match the token's clock. Fallback to block numbers if the token does not implement ERC-6372.

params._name: The name of the governor instance
params._timelock: The timelock controller for proposal execution
params._token: The token used for voting (ERC20Votes or ERC721Votes)

getVotes(address,uint256).details: See {IGovernor-getVotes}. Returns the voting power of an account at a specific block number.

params.account: The address to get voting power for
params.blockNumber: The block number to get the votes at

returns._0: The voting power of the account at the given block

hashProposal(address[],uint256[],bytes[].details: See {IGovernor-hashProposal}. The proposal id is produced by hashing the ABI encoded `targets` array, the `values` array, the `calldatas` array and the descriptionHash (bytes32 which itself is the keccak256 hash of the description string). This proposal id can be produced from the proposal data which is part of the {ProposalCreated} event. It can even be computed in advance, before the proposal is submitted. Note that the chainId and the governor address are not part of the proposal id computation. Consequently, the same proposal (with same operation and same description) will have the same id if submitted on multiple governors across multiple networks. This also means that in order to execute the same operation twice (on the same governor) the proposer will have to change the description in order to avoid proposal id conflicts.

nonces(address).details: Returns the next unused nonce for an address.

onERC1155BatchReceived(address,address,u.details: See {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155BatchReceived}. Receiving tokens is disabled if the governance executor is other than the governor itself (eg. when using with a timelock).

onERC1155Received(address,address,uint25.details: See {IERC1155Receiver-onERC1155Received}. Receiving tokens is disabled if the governance executor is other than the governor itself (eg. when using with a timelock).

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: See {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}. Receiving tokens is disabled if the governance executor is other than the governor itself (eg. when using with a timelock).

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proposalAllVotes(uint256).details: Returns all vote counts for a proposal. The array order is: Against, For, Abstain, Option 0, Option 1, ..., Option N-1.

proposalNeedsQueuing(uint256).details: Returns whether a proposal needs to be queued through the timelock.

returns._0: True if the proposal needs queuing, false otherwise

proposalOptionVotes(uint256,uint8).details: Returns the vote counts for a specific option.

params.optionIndex: The index of the option to get votes for

returns.optionVotes: The number of votes for the specified option

proposalOptions(uint256).details: Returns the options associated with a proposal.

proposalThreshold().details: Returns the proposal threshold required for creating new proposals. Resolves the diamond inheritance between Governor and GovernorSettings.

returns._0: The proposal threshold (minimum votes required to create a proposal)

proposalVotes(uint256).details: Accessor to the internal vote counts.

propose(address[],uint256[],bytes[],stri.details: See {IGovernor-propose}. Standard proposal creation without multiple choice options.

params.calldatas: The calldata to send with each call
params.targets: The addresses of the contracts to call
params.values: The ETH values to send with each call

returns.proposalId: The ID of the newly created proposal

propose(address[],uint256[],bytes[],stri.details: Overload for proposing with multiple choice options.

params.calldatas: The calldata to send with each call
params.options: The array of option descriptions for the multiple choice proposal
params.targets: The addresses of the contracts to call
params.values: The ETH values to send with each call

returns.proposalId: The ID of the newly created proposal

quorum(uint256).details: See {IGovernor-quorum}. Returns the minimum number of votes required for a proposal to succeed.

params.blockNumber: The block number to get the quorum at

returns._0: The minimum number of votes required for quorum

quorumDenominator().details: Returns the quorum denominator. Defaults to 100, but may be overridden.

quorumNumerator().details: Returns the current quorum numerator. See {quorumDenominator}.

quorumNumerator(uint256).details: Returns the quorum numerator at a specific timepoint. See {quorumDenominator}.

relay(address,uint256,bytes).details: Relays a transaction or function call to an arbitrary target. In cases where the governance executor is some contract other than the governor itself, like when using a timelock, this function can be invoked in a governance proposal to recover tokens or Ether that was sent to the governor contract by mistake. Note that if the executor is simply the governor itself, use of `relay` is redundant.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setEvaluator(address).details: Sets or updates the address of the evaluator contract. Only callable by the owner.

params._newEvaluator: The address of the new evaluator contract

setProposalThreshold(uint256).details: Update the proposal threshold. This operation can only be performed through a governance proposal. Emits a {ProposalThresholdSet} event.

setVotingDelay(uint48).details: Update the voting delay. This operation can only be performed through a governance proposal. Emits a {VotingDelaySet} event.

setVotingPeriod(uint32).details: Update the voting period. This operation can only be performed through a governance proposal. Emits a {VotingPeriodSet} event.

state(uint256).details: See {IGovernor-state}. Returns the current state of a proposal.

returns._0: True if the contract supports the interface

timelock().details: Public accessor to check the address of the timelock

token().details: The token that voting power is sourced from.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateQuorumNumerator(uint256).details: Changes the quorum numerator. Emits a {QuorumNumeratorUpdated} event. Requirements: - Must be called through a governance proposal. - New numerator must be smaller or equal to the denominator.

updateTimelock(address).details: Public endpoint to update the underlying timelock instance. Restricted to the timelock itself, so updates must be proposed, scheduled, and executed through governance proposals. CAUTION: It is not recommended to change the timelock while there are other queued governance proposals.

votingDelay().details: See {IGovernor-votingDelay}. Returns the delay before voting on a proposal may start.

votingPeriod().details: See {IGovernor-votingPeriod}. Returns the period during which votes can be cast.
